thread.title: Mason, Starkjohann share lead in Senior PGA Professional
thread.title_full: Mason, Starkjohann share lead in Senior PGA Professional | Boston Herald

author: Associated Press
title: Mason, Starkjohann share lead in Senior PGA Professional
text:
SEASIDE, Calif. â€” James Mason shot a 3-under 69 for a share of the lead with Chris Starkjohann on Friday in the Senior PGA Professional National Championship
The 64-year-old Mason is a PGA Life Member from Dillard, Georgia, who finished second last season. He holed out from 60 yards for eagle on the par-5 12th hole at Black Horse.
The top 35 finishers will earn spots in the Senior PGA Championship in May at Harbor Shores in Benton Harbor, Michigan. The final two rounds will played on the Bayonet Course.
The 59-year-old Starkjohann, from Oceanside, California, had a 70 at Black Horse to match Mason at 7-under 137. Rick Morton of Jacksonville, North Carolina, was a stroke back after a 70 at Black Horse.
